(1, 'Easy Tiramisu (Raw-Egg-Free) Recipe', '2021-02-23 00:00:00', 'food-posts-1', 'yvonnemeetsfood', 'yvonnemeetsfood@gmail.com', 'This is by no means \"authentic\" tiramisu in that it has no raw eggs, but it\'s just as tasty!\r\n\r\n**Easy Tiramisu Recipe (no raw eggs!)**\r\n\r\n**Ingredients:** \r\n\r\n* About 1.5 packages worth of lady fingers (I got mine at an Italian market, ran out, and then had my husband run out to get more at Whole Foods - he got the store-brand, which is also imported from Italy). Make sure these are the HARD lady fingers, NOT the soft ones!\r\n* 2 C strong coffee/espresso\r\n* 9 Tbsp rum or marsala wine (you can half this for a less pronounced alcoholic flavor; I thought this was just right :)\r\n* 1 C heavy cream\r\n* 1-1.5 lb mascarpone\r\n* 2/3 C sugar, divided\r\n* 1 tsp vanilla extract\r\n* 2-3 Tbsp cocoa powder\r\n* Handful of chopped chocolate/chocolate shavings (optional)\r\n\r\n**Method:** \r\n\r\n1. **Prepare coffee/alcohol for dipping:** Combine coffee in a wide, shallow bowl, and combine with about 5 Tbsp of the rum. Set side.\r\n2. **Prepare mascarpone/cream mixture:** Whip heavy cream with 1/3 C sugar, 1 tsp vanilla extract, and 2 Tbsp rum, until you have soft peaks. Then, slowly fold in the mascarpone along with the other 1/3 C sugar and 2 Tbsp rum. Whip altogether until nice and fluffy. Set aside.\r\n3. **Prepare tiramisu layers:** Dip each side of a lady finger into the coffee/rum mixture for no more than 1-2 seconds per side (DO NOT DIP TOO LONG; This is the biggest mistake in making tiramisu. NO SOGGINESS!). Then, carefully lay in a pan (8x5 in), making sure all the ladyfingers are lined up side by side; trim if needed to fix snuggly into pan. Then, add a generous, even layer of the mascarpone/cream mixture on top of the ladyfingers, smoothing them out on the edges with a spatula. Dust with some cocoa powder with a colander/sieve. Repeat the ladyfinger layer with the final mascarpone layer, and dust the top with cocoa powder and chocolate shavings if using.\r\n4. **Refrigerate tiramisu** for at least 6 hours to allow it to set, and allowing the lady fingers to soften well. Cut with a clean knife, wiping off between slices for the cleanest edges, and enjoy!', 'rye-dinner-rolls-with-crisp-tops-352316.jpg', 2044),
(2, 'I was inspired by the Thai Ramen posted here earlier and made a Spicy Thai Shrimp Noodle Soup with Charred Tatsoi!', '2021-02-23 00:00:00', 'food-posts-2', 'BushyEyes', 'BushyEyes@gmail.com', 'Thank you for the great idea, u/oliveyoil!\r\n\r\n**Recipe here originally:** [**Spicy Thai Shrimp Noodle Soup**](https://www.triedandtruerecipe.com/2021/02/23/spicy-thai-shrimp-noodle-soup/)\r\n\r\nThis spicy Thai shrimp noodle soup is an explosion of heat and rich flavor paired with beautifully charred greens.\r\n\r\nPrep Time: 15 minutes\r\n\r\nCook Time: 30 minutes\r\n\r\nTotal Time: 45 minutes\r\n\r\nServings: 4\r\n\r\nCalories: 542kcal\r\n\r\nAuthor: Kylie Perrotti\r\n\r\nEquipment\r\n\r\n* Large pot\r\n* Medium pot\r\n* Sheet pan\r\n* Strainer or sieve\r\n\r\nIngredientsBroth and Noodles:\r\n\r\n* 2 tablespoons neutral oil for frying\r\n* 1 yellow onion peeled and thinly sliced\r\n* 4 cloves garlic peeled and minced\r\n* 1-3 Thai chili peppers trimmed and minced (adjust quantity based on spice preference)\r\n* 4 scallions white parts minced, green parts thinly sliced on an angle\r\n* 2 tablespoons Thai curry paste red, green, or yellow\r\n* 6 cups chicken stock\r\n* 1 tablespoon fish sauce or less, depending on preference\r\n* 2 tablespoons sugar\r\n* 8 ounces vermicelli noodles\r\n* Salt and pepper to taste\r\n\r\nShrimp and Vegetables:\r\n\r\n* 1 pound jumbo shrimp peeled and deveined, tails discarded or kept on depending on preference\r\n* 1 pint cherry tomatoes\r\n* 1 lime juiced\r\n* 2 tablespoons avocado oil\r\n* 1 tablespoon fish sauce\r\n* 1 tablespoon soy sauce\r\n* 1 tablespoon sugar\r\n* 1 teaspoon sesame oil\r\n* ¼ teaspoon salt optional\r\n* 1 bunch tatsoi or 4 heads baby bok choy, halved lengthwise\r\n\r\nInstructionsCook the Broth Aromatics:\r\n\r\n* Heat the oil in a large pot over medium heat. Add the onion and cook for 5 minutes until just beginning to turn translucent.\r\n* Add the garlic, Thai chili pepper, and minced white parts of the scallions and cook for 1 minute until fragrant.\r\n* Add the curry paste and lightly mash it into the oil. Cook for 2-3 minutes until fragrant.\r\n\r\nSimmer the Broth:\r\n\r\n* Pour in the chicken stock. Add the sugar and fish sauce and bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover, and simmer for 30 minutes. Taste and season to your preferences. Keep warm.\r\n\r\nMarinate the Shrimp:\r\n\r\n* In a bowl, combine the lime juice, avocado oil, fish sauce, soy sauce, sugar, and sesame oil and whisk to combine. Add the shrimp and tomatoes to the bowl. Sprinkle with a ¼ teaspoon salt. Toss to coat. Transfer to the refrigerator for 15 minutes.\r\n\r\nCook the Noodles:\r\n\r\n* Bring a medium pot of water to a boil. Add the noodles and cook according to package instructions (typically 2-4 minutes for vermicelli). Drain and rinse thoroughly with cold water. Set aside. If needed, refresh the noodles with cold water before serving but if you time it correctly, they should only be sitting in the strainer for a few minutes.\r\n\r\nBroil the Shrimp:\r\n\r\n* Turn the broiler on. Pour the shrimp and excess marinade onto the sheet pan and arrange the shrimp and tomatoes in an even layer on half the sheet pan. Place the tatsoi on the other half of the sheet pan and sprinkle with salt and add a drizzle of oil.\r\n* Transfer the sheet pan to the oven and broil for 4-5 minutes until the shrimp are just cooked through and the tatsoi is charred and the tomatoes have just begun the split open.\r\n\r\nTo Serve:\r\n\r\n* Divide the cooked noodles between bowls. Ladle the broth on top. Arrange the shrimp, tomatoes, and tatsoi on top. Garnish with the thinly sliced scallion greens. Enjoy!\r\n\r\nNutrition\r\n\r\nCalories: 542kcal | Carbohydrates: 73g | Protein: 35g | Fat: 13g | Saturated Fat: 2g | Cholesterol: 286mg | Sodium: 2211mg | Potassium: 811mg | Fiber: 3g | Sugar: 15g | Vitamin A: 1898IU | Vitamin C: 44mg | Calcium: 243mg | Iron: 5mg', 'apricot-date-and-pistachio-haroseth-352324.jpg', 3490),
(3, 'Homemade Cinnamon Rolls Recipe', '2021-02-22 00:00:00', 'food-posts-3', 'pangibear', 'pangibear@gmail.com', '**Homemade Cinnamon Rolls**\r\n\r\nLayers of soft chewy dough, with brown sugar cinnamon between each one, topped with a cream cheese frosting, all swirled into one treat.\r\n\r\n### INGREDIENTS \r\n\r\n#### Cinnamon Roll Dough\r\n\r\n* 1 c warm milk (not hot)\r\n* 2-1/2 tsp Instant yeast\r\n* 1/2 c granulated sugar\r\n* 2 large eggs, at room temperature\r\n* 1/4 c butter, melted\r\n* 1 tsp vanilla extract\r\n* 1 tsp salt\r\n* 4 c flour\r\n\r\n#### Filling\r\n\r\n* 3/4 c brown sugar, packed\r\n* 2 Tbsp cinnamon\r\n* 1/2 c butter, softened\r\n\r\n#### Icing\r\n\r\n* 6 oz cream cheese, softened\r\n* 1-1/2 c powdered sugar\r\n* 1/3 c butter, melted\r\n* 1 tsp vanilla extract\r\n\r\n### INSTRUCTIONS \r\n\r\n#### Making the Dough\r\n\r\n* Place warm milk in a mixing bowl, add yeast, and give it a stir. Let it sit for a minute or two while you�re gathering your other ingredients. \r\n* Next, add sugar, eggs, butter, salt, and vanilla, and mix well. Lastly, using a dough hook, add flour and mix until it forms a firm yet tacky dough that pulls away from the edges. Resist adding more flour&the dough should be slightly tacky.\r\n* Remove dough from the mixer and knead by hand, on a lightly floured surface, for 5 minutes (yes, even if you used a stand mixer).\r\n\r\n#### First Rising\r\n\r\n* Grease a large bowl with butter or cooking spray. Place the dough in this bowl, cover with a warm towel, and let sit in a warm spot for 1 to 1-½ hours or until it doubles in size.\r\n\r\n#### Cinnamon Roll Filling\r\n\r\n* In a bowl, mix together brown sugar, cinnamon, and softened butter until it resembles a paste.\r\n\r\n#### Rolling out the dough, adding filling, and cutting into shape\r\n\r\n* For this step, I used silicone baking mats, but you can also roll out the dough on a lightly floured surface. With a lightly floured rolling pin, roll out the dough into a rectangle, measuring approximately 22� x 14�.\r\n* Drop some of the cinnamon roll filling here and there over the rolled out dough. Then, using a rubber spatula, gently spread the filling all over the dough, keeping away from the edges by about a quarter inch.\r\n* Starting at a short end (one of the 14� ends), gently but tightly roll the dough into one long roll.\r\n* Using a sharp knife (I found that a serrated knife worked best), cut the roll into 12 evenly sliced pieces. \r\n\r\n#### Second Rising\r\n\r\n* Preheat oven to 350	.\r\n* Place the cut cinnamon rolls into a parchment-lined baking dish, three rows of four. Cover the dish with plastic wrap and let the rolls rise for another 30 minutes, or until they�ve nearly doubled in size.\r\n\r\n#### Baking Cinnamon Rolls\r\n\r\n* Remove the plastic wrap and place baking pan in the oven on the middle rack. Bake for 20 � 30 minutes. My cinnamon rolls took 30 minutes to bake, but you should start checking on them after 20 minutes. All ovens are different. The cinnamon rolls will be done when the tops have just lightly browned and the dough sounds hollow when you lightly tap on it with a spoon. The rolls will rise even more while they�re baking and will most likely touch each other. This is fine and good&they�ll stay soft in the middle.\r\n\r\n#### Icing for Cinnamon Rolls\r\n\r\n* While the rolls are baking, make the icing. Using either a stand mixer or handheld mixer, blend together cream cheese, powdered sugar, butter, and vanilla until smooth. \r\n* When the cinnamon rolls are done baking, let them cool about 5 minutes and add icing to the tops, so it will slightly melt and ooze between the swirls. If you prefer the icing thicker on top, wait until they�ve fully cooled.', 'deviled-ham-and-pickle-sandwiches-352286.jpg', 3432),
(4, 'Classic Creme Brulee at home with only 4 ingredients! Why isn\'t everyone making this?', '2021-02-22 00:00:00', 'food-posts-4', 'Doesntpayfullprice', 'Doesntpayfullprice@gmail.com', 'One of my favorite at home dessert recipes! Enjoy. You can also watch my fun step-by-step video here [https://youtu.be/9pB0X-ibfqM](https://youtu.be/9pB0X-ibfqM) if your into that sort of thing.\r\n\r\n**Creme Brulee**\r\n\r\nServes 2-4\r\n\r\nIngredients:\r\n\r\n3 egg yolks\r\n\r\n1 Cup heavy cream\r\n\r\n2 Tablespoons sugar + 1 teaspoon for bruleeing\r\n\r\n1/2 teaspoon vanilla\r\n\r\n**How To:**\r\n\r\n* In a heatproof bowl combine egg yolks and sugar, whisk vigorously for 2-5 minutes until color turns a pale yellow.\r\n* add vanilla\r\n* In a small saucepot heat the cream until it just comes to a boil and remove from heat.\r\n* Slowly a few tablespoons at a time, whisk hot cream into egg yolk mixture to *temper* the eggs.\r\n* Once all the cream in incorporated place heatproof bowl on top of a double boiler (small pan with about an inch of water brought to a boil) \\*Make sure the water doesnt touch the bottom of the bowl or it will get too hot.\r\n* Stir with a spatula for 5 minutes or until the mixture thickens to coat the back of a spoon.\r\n* remove from heat and add to your ramekins.\r\n* Place ramekins in a high sided brownie pan or casserole dish and place in the middle of a 325 degree oven.\r\n* Pour hot water into the brownie pan, making sure not to get any in the ramekins. Water should come half way up the sides of the ramekins.\r\n* Bake for 30 minutes or until set, but still a little wobbly.\r\n* Let cool for 2 hours minimum.\r\n* Sugar the top and dump off any excess, torch until crispy and golden amber, or place under the broiler set to high.\r\n* Enjoy!\r\n\r\n\\*The sugar for bruleeing works better if it is *sugar in the raw,* granulated sugar burns too fast and wont form a good crust.', 'saffron-rice-pilaf-352325.jpg', 1639),
(5, 'Thai Ramen with Tumeric Shrimp', '2021-02-22 00:00:00', 'food-posts-5', 'oliveyoil', 'oliveyoil@gmail.com', 'I am obsessed with making different ramen dishes while restaurants are closed! This shrimp ramen with a golden turmeric hue is definitely one of my favourites so far.\r\n\r\nHere is the [link to the original recipe](https://www.kitchenful.com/lp/recipe/Thai-Ramen-with-Tumeric-Shrimp-4016/rf).\r\n\r\n&amp;#x200B;\r\n\r\n**Ingredients:**\r\n\r\n2 package instant ramen noodles \r\n\r\n2.5 cup  water \r\n\r\n2  tomatoes \r\n\r\n1 clove  garlic \r\n\r\n2 tbsp  olive oil \r\n\r\n6 oz  shrimp \r\n\r\n2 oz  mushrooms \r\n\r\n3 tbsp  thai chili paste \r\n\r\n2 tbsp  soy sauce \r\n\r\n1 cup  coconut mik \r\n\r\n1 tsp  paprika \r\n\r\n1 tsp  turmeric \r\n\r\nsalt \r\n\r\nblack pepper \r\n\r\ncilantro \r\n\r\n&amp;#x200B;\r\n\r\n**Directions:**\r\n\r\nChop the mushrooms and garlic. Cut the tomatoes into wedges. If the shrimp has shells still, shell and devein them. \r\n\r\nHeat 1 tbsp olive oil in a large saucepan. Add the garlic and mushroom and cook until brown. Stir in the chili paste.\r\n\r\nPour in the coconut milk and water and bring to a boil. Season with salt and pepper.\r\n\r\nSeason the shrimp with salt, pepper, paprika, and turmeric.\r\n\r\nHeat 1 tbsp olive oil in a skillet. Add the shrimp and cook just until pink, 2-4 minutes on each side. Set aside.\r\n\r\nAdd the noodles to the saucepan and cook according to packaging instructions. Serve ramen with shrimp. Sprinkle freshly chopped cilantro and serve.', 'glazed-pearl-onions-and-grapes-352278.jpg', 1270),
(6, 'Vanilla-shallot butter poached monkfish', '2021-02-22 00:00:00', 'food-posts-6', 'notanonlyfans', 'notanonlyfans@gmail.com', 'Purchased monkfish for a hotpot, but my fishmonger recommended I try out this instead! Monkfish has a meaty texture and tastes similar to lobster. The vanilla really enhanced the flavors; the poaching liquid was based on a [Langouste à la Vanille recipe](https://www.saveur.com/lobster-vanilla-sauce-recipe/)\r\n\r\n**Ingredients**\r\n\r\n- monkfish filet, membrane removed (3/4lb)\r\n- unsalted butter, cut into Tbsp slices (2 sticks)\r\n- shallot, roughly minced (1)\r\n- white wine (1/4-1/2 cup)\r\n- vanilla extract (2 tsp)\r\n\r\n**Directions**\r\n\r\n1. Prepare all your ingredients, remove the membrane on the monkfish if still attached (not necessary but I find it can be tough cooked)\r\n\r\n2. Heat 1-2 Tbsp water in a nonstick skillet on medium heat until sizzling\r\n\r\n3. Add butter to the hot skillet several Tbsp at a time, when melted add in shallot, white wine, and vanilla, bring to a low simmer\r\n\r\n4. Add monkfish filet to your poaching liquid\r\n\r\n5. Spooning liquid over the filet, poach for 3-5 minutes per side, flipping once (depends on your thickness). Alternately if you have a thermometer, cook to 140-150\r\n\r\n6. Serve &amp; spoon excess poaching liquid over fish &amp; whatever sides you prefer', 'herb-roasted-pork-loin-352314.jpg', 1166),
(7, 'Italian Meatballs', '2021-02-21 00:00:00', 'food-posts-7', 'R_Whats_For_Dinner', 'R_Whats_For_Dinner@gmail.com', 'Ingredients: \r\n\r\n1. Ground beef (1.8 lb / 800 g) \r\n\r\n2. Cottage cheese (0.4 lb / 200 g) \r\n\r\n3. Italian bread crumbs (1/2 cup) \r\n\r\n4. Parsley \r\n\r\n5. Lemon zest (from one lemon) \r\n\r\n6. Cheese (0.05 lb / 25 g) \r\n\r\n7. Egg (1 piece) \r\n\r\n8. Onion (1 medium onion) \r\n\r\n9. Garlic (2 cloves) \r\n\r\n10. Basil (1 tsp) \r\n\r\n11. Canned tomatoes (1 can) \r\n\r\n12. Balsamic vinegar (2 tbsp) \r\n\r\n13. Broth (4 oz / 120 g) \r\n\r\n14. Salt \r\n\r\nCooking method (video recipe is [here](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IaZ9El4XdQg)): \r\n\r\n1.Miix the ground beef, cottage cheese, bread crumbs, salt, parsley, lemon zest, cheese, egg and knead \r\n\r\n2. Fry the onion, garlic and basil for 3 minutes \r\n\r\n3. Combine the mixture with minced meat and knead \r\n\r\n4. Form meatballs \r\n\r\n5. Fry for 3 minutes on each side \r\n\r\n6. Mix canned tomatoes, broth and balsamic vinegar and after boiling put meatballs \r\n\r\n7. Close and fry for 15 minutes \r\n\r\n8. Delicious italian meatballs are ready!', 'mediterranean-grilled-lamb-steaks-352276.jpg', 900),
(8, 'Red Lentils and Spinach Lasagna, what do you think?', '2021-02-21 00:00:00', 'food-posts-8', 'SupraWorldly', 'SupraWorldly@gmail.com', '\\*\\*Spinach Lasagna\\*\\*:  \r\n\r\n\\*\\*Ingredients\\*\\*:  \r\n\r\n \\* 1 Pack (Instant) Lasagna Pasta\r\n\r\n \\* 1 Pack Frozen Spinach\r\n\r\n \\* (optional) red lentils\r\n\r\n \\* 200ml Soy cream\r\n\r\n \\* Tomato Sauce  \r\n\r\n \\* 150g Shredded Mozzarella Cheese\r\n\r\n \\* 1/2 Onion \r\n\r\n \\* Chopped Garlic Clove\r\n\r\nCooking Instructions:\r\n\r\n1. **Start with the sauce**: in this recipe I like to use a combination of red lentils and tomato sauce\r\n2. **Make the white cream**: in a pan fry the chopped onion and garlic, in a bit of Olive oil for about 2 minutes. Then pour the soy cream and let it steer for around 8-10minutes. \r\n3. **Grab the lasagna pasta**: follow the instruction on the pasta box for having it ready. \r\n4. **Layer it u**p: Start with a little sauce in the bottom of the pan to ensure your noodles don�t stick to the bottom, then top with noodles, cream, and sauce and then repeat. Dump allllll of that extra mozzarella on the top for good measure!\r\n5. **Cover and bak**e: Covering the lasagna with foil to bake ensures that the moisture stays inside and cooks the noodles. We will uncover once we add the cheese and let it sit at room temperature for some time before slicing to help it set well.\r\n\r\nEnjoy!', 'avgolemono-352269.jpg', 1164),
(9, 'Soft and Chewy Snickerdoodle Cookie Bars', '2021-02-21 00:00:00', 'food-posts-9', 'cookingsheri', 'cookingsheri@gmail.com', '**Ingredients** \r\n\r\n* Nonstick cooking spray \r\n* 2 sticks (1 cup) unsalted butter, at room temperature \r\n* 1 cup granulated sugar \r\n* 3/4 cup packed light brown sugar \r\n* 2 large eggs \r\n* 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla extract \r\n* 2 1/2 cups all-purpose flour \r\n* 1 teaspoon baking powder \r\n* 3/4 teaspoon salt \r\n\r\n**Cinnamon Mixture**\r\n\r\n* 1/4 cup granulated sugar \r\n* 3 teaspoons ground cinnamon\r\n\r\n**Glaze**\r\n\r\n* 1 cup powdered sugar\r\n* 2 tablespoons milk\r\n* 1/4 teaspoon vanilla\r\n\r\n**Steps**\r\n\r\n1. Heat oven to 350° F. Spray bottom of a 13x9-inch baking pan with cooking spray. In bowl, combine flour, baking powder, and salt, set aside.\r\n2. In large bowl, beat butter with both sugars until creamy. Gradually beat in eggs and vanilla into sugar mixture until combined. On low speed, slowly mix in dry ingredients until combined.\r\n3. Spoon half the batter into pan and spread evenly. Sprinkle cinnamon-sugar mixture evenly over batter.\r\n4. Dollop teaspoon size amounts of remaining batter evenly over cinnamon-sugar mixture.\r\n5. Bake 25 minutes or until golden brown. Cool completely. \r\n6. In small bowl, stir glaze ingredients until smooth and thin. Drizzle over bars. Cut bars into 6x4 rows.\r\n\r\nIf you\'d like to watch me make these bars, you can watch it [here](https://youtu.be/KIVhPdvEgk8)!', 'simple-spring-green-salad-352285.jpg', 1260),
(10, 'Thai Holy Basil Chicken Stir-Fry with a Crispy Fried Egg (Pad Krapow)', '2021-02-21 00:00:00', 'food-posts-10', 'danos95', 'danos95@gmail.com', 'This dish is often a firm favourite for all Thai food lovers. It\'s really simple to make and requires only a little prep time. The hardest part is finding Holy basil! I\'m based in the UK where I can find it from Chinatown in London - I\'m not sure of it\'s availability in the US but I\'m sure East Asian grocers will stock in in places or it can be ordered online. If you can\'t find holy basil, it\'s better to use normal Italian basil instead as opposed to using Thai basil which has a aniseedy flavour.\r\n\r\nPrep Time: 20 minutes\r\n\r\nCook Time: 10 mins\r\n\r\nTotal Time: 30 mins\r\n\r\nServings: 1\r\n\r\n###### EQUIPMENT\r\n\r\n- Wok or Large Frying Pan\r\n\r\n###### INGREDIENTS\r\n\r\n\" 150g chicken thigh, cut into chunks\r\n\r\n\" 2 tbs veg oil \r\n\r\n\" 2 tbs oyster saucec  \r\n\" 8 birdseye chillies  \r\n\" 4 cloves of garlic  \r\n\" 1/2 tsp dark soy sauce  \r\n\" 1/2 tsp light soy sauce  \r\n\" 1/2 tsp white sugar  \r\n\" 1/2 cup holy basil leaves\r\n\r\n\" 1 cup cooked Jasmine rice  \r\n\" 1 egg\r\n\r\nHere is a [video](https://www.instagram.com/p/CLfJA6ppiEh/) of the cooking process (NB if you don\'t have Instagram give me a shout and I can upload to imgur). Otherwise below are detailed steps on how to make this dish.  \r\n  \r\n\r\n###### INSTRUCTIONS \r\n\r\n- Marinate the chicken in oyster sauce for at least 30 mins - this will help tenderise the meat.\r\n- Pound chillies and garlic into a coarse paste using a mortar and pestle. If you dont have a mortar and pestle, finely chopping each is fine. \r\n- In a hot wok or large frying pan, add veg oil and then chicken, stir fry over high heat for about 4 minutes until chicken is about 80% cooked through.\r\n- Add chillies and garlic, stir fry for 1 min \r\n- Season with dark and light soy and pinch of sugar.\r\n- Turn heat down, add holy basil and fold it through until just wilted. Serve on top of freshly cooked jasmine rice\r\n- In a hot frying pan or wok add plenty of oil and fry egg until crispy but still soft yolk (about 2 mins). Add egg on top of rice and chicken. \r\n\r\n###### TO SERVE\r\n\r\n- This dish is spicy and there is nothing better to accompany it then an ice cold beer!', 'almond-olive-oil-tuiles-352327.jpg', 2028),
(11, 'Almond Sandies', '2021-02-20 00:00:00', 'food-posts-11', 'TheGreatOldOne1917', 'TheGreatOldOne1917@gmail.com', 'Ingredients\r\n\r\n* 1 cup (240ml) all-purpose flour\r\n* 1 cup (240ml) sliced almonds\r\n* 1 stick (120ml) room temperature butter\r\n* 1/2 cup (120ml) brown sugar\r\n* 1 1/2 teaspoon (7.5ml) almond extract\r\n* 1/4 teaspoon (1ml) salt\r\n\r\nDirections\r\n\r\n1. Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C).\r\n2. Combine all ingredients together in a mixing bowl.\r\n3. Mix with a hand mixer until a solid dough forms and the almonds are broken up.\r\n4. Roll into approximately 9 equal sized balls (smaller if you want smaller cookies) and place on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.\r\n5. Flatten all the balls slightly until they\'re roughly 1cm thick.\r\n6. Bake for 15 minutes.\r\n7. Allow to cool and dust with powdered sugar or serve as is.\r\n\r\nSource: [here\'s a link to the blog post](https://justthedarnrecipe.com/almond-sandies) if you\'re interested in that.', 'hot-toddy-pudding-cake-352319.jpg', 810),
(12, 'Folded Sushi - Alaska Roll', '2021-02-20 00:00:00', 'food-posts-12', 'grubbingwithguber', 'grubbingwithguber@gmail.com', 'Craving for some sushi but don\'t have a sushi roller? Try this easy version instead. It\'s super easy yet equally delicious!\r\n\r\n[Video Recipe](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1LJPS1lOHSM)\r\n\r\n# Ingredients\r\n\r\nServing Size:  \\~5 sandwiches      \r\n\r\n* 1 cup of sushi rice\r\n* 3/4 cups + 2 1/2 tbsp of water\r\n* A small piece of konbu (kelp)\r\n* 2 tbsp of rice vinegar\r\n* 1 tbsp of sugar\r\n* 1 tsp of salt\r\n* 2 avocado\r\n* 6 imitation crab sticks\r\n* 2 tbsp of Japanese mayo\r\n* 1/2 lb of salmon  \r\n\r\n# Recipe     \r\n\r\n* Place 1 cup of sushi rice into a mixing bowl and wash the rice at least 2 times or until the water becomes clear. Then transfer the rice into the rice cooker and add a small piece of kelp along with 3/4 cups plus 2 1/2 tbsp of water. Cook according to your rice cookers instruction.\r\n* Combine 2 tbsp rice vinegar, 1 tbsp sugar, and 1 tsp salt in a medium bowl. Mix until everything is well combined.\r\n* After the rice is cooked, remove the kelp and immediately scoop all the rice into the medium bowl with the vinegar and mix it well using the rice spatula. Make sure to use the cut motion to mix the rice to avoid mashing them. After thats done, cover it with a kitchen towel and let it cool down to room temperature.\r\n* Cut the top of 1 avocado, then slice into the center of the avocado and rotate it along your knife. Then take each half of the avocado and twist. Afterward, take the side with the pit and carefully chop into the pit and twist to remove it. Then, using your hand, remove the peel. Repeat these steps with the other avocado. Dont forget to clean up your work station to give yourself more space. Then, place each half of the avocado facing down and thinly slice them. Once theyre sliced, slowly spread them out. Once thats done, set it aside.\r\n* Remove the wrapper from each crab stick. Then, using your hand, peel the crab sticks vertically to get strings of crab sticks. Once all the crab sticks are peeled, rotate them sideways and chop them into small pieces, then place them in a bowl along with 2 tbsp of Japanese mayo and mix until everything is well mixed.\r\n* Place a sharp knife at an angle and thinly slice against the grain. The thickness of the cut depends on your preference. Just make sure that all the pieces are similar in thickness.\r\n* Grab a piece of seaweed wrap. Using a kitchen scissor, start cutting at the halfway point of seaweed wrap and cut until youre a little bit past the center of the piece. Rotate the piece vertically and start building. Dip your hand in some water to help with the sushi rice. Take a handful of sushi rice and spread it around the upper left hand quadrant of the seaweed wrap. Then carefully place a couple slices of salmon on the top right quadrant. Then place a couple slices of avocado on the bottom right quadrant. And finish it off with a couple of tsp of crab salad on the bottom left quadrant. Then, fold the top right quadrant into the bottom right quadrant, then continue by folding it into the bottom left quadrant. Well finish off the folding by folding the top left quadrant onto the rest of the sandwich. Afterward, place a piece of plastic wrap on top, cut it half, add a couple pieces of ginger and wasabi, and there you have it.', 'lemon-snow-pudding-with-basil-custard-sauce-352321.jpg', 3203),
(13, 'Cabbage soup', '2021-02-20 00:00:00', 'food-posts-13', 'R_Whats_For_Dinner', 'R_Whats_For_Dinner@gmail.com', 'Ingredients:\r\n\r\n1. Onion (1/2 onion)\r\n2. Garlic (2 cloves)\r\n3. Grated ginger (1 tsp)\r\n4. Celery (3 stalks)\r\n5. Cabbage (1/2 kacana)\r\n6. Chicken broth (5 cups)\r\n7. Frozen spinach (0.6lb / 300g), can be replaced with fresh\r\n8. Parsley (1/2 cup)\r\n9. Paprika (1/2 tsp)\r\n10. Boiled chicken (1 cup), optional\r\n11. Olive oil\r\n12. Salt\r\n\r\nCooking method:\r\n\r\n1. Fry onion, garlic, ginger in olive oil until the onion is soft (2-3 minutes)\r\n2. Add celery, fry for 1 minute, add salt and cabbage, fry for another 2 minutes\r\n3. Add broth, spinach and cook for one minute after boiling\r\n4. Add parsley, paprika and chicken (optional) and cook for another 1 minute\r\n\r\nYou can see how I made this soup [here](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=klvuqjAWvXg)', 'bibimbap-352271.jpg', 716),
(14, 'Fried Banana Balls (Kuih Kodok)', '2021-02-20 00:00:00', 'food-posts-14', 'juicyorange520', 'juicyorange520@gmail.com', 'The original recipe with more images and instructions video can be found [here](https://www.mylovelyrecipes.com/recipes/asian-cuisine/kuih-kodok/)\r\n\r\n&amp;nbsp;\r\n\r\n#####Preparation time: 15 minutes\r\n#####Cooking time: 5 minutes\r\n#####Serving size: about 8 pieces\r\n\r\n&amp;nbsp;\r\n\r\n#INGREDIENTS\r\n- 200g Peeled Banana\r\n- 50g All-purpose Flour\r\n- 1 tbsp Sugar\r\n- 0.25 tsp Salt\r\n- 0.25 tsp Baking Soda\r\n\r\n&amp;nbsp;\r\n\r\n#INSTRUCTIONS\r\n1. Add salt, baking soda, and sugar after mashing the banana.\r\n2. Add the sifted flour and mix well.\r\n3. Rest the batter for about 10 minutes.\r\n4. Pour oil into the pot, scoop into the banana batter after the oil temperature is hot, and fry it until light brown color.\r\n5. Let cool and enjoy.', 'creamy-grits-with-rosemary-bacon-352275.jpg', 697),
(15, 'Crunchy Cauliflower Bites &amp; Tikka Masala Dip', '2021-02-20 00:00:00', 'food-posts-15', 'mienczaczek', 'mienczaczek@gmail.com', 'Super crunchy fried cauliflower bites with smooth and delicate tikka masala sauce, perfect starter or a snack that you can prepare in no time! Just grab one floret and dip it in the sauce :)\r\n\r\n### What is Tikka Masala sauce and where it comes from?\r\n\r\nThe history of this popular sauce is not 100% clear, some say it was created in India while others say it was created in the UK by Bangladeshi migrant Chefs. Whoever did it, did a good job, the sauce is one of the most popular in the world thanks to its mild and delicate flavour. In short, it is the smooth tomato-based curry sauce with the addition of **garam masala** and finished with yoghurt. The sauce is usually served with dry roasted marinated chicken or lamb (Tikka). From my experience, every Chef prepares it differently, what are your experiences with this sauce?\r\n\r\n### Ingredients for Tikka Masala sauce:\r\n\r\n* 1tbsp butter\r\n* 1 banana shallot, finely diced\r\n* 2 garlic cloves, minced\r\n* 1tsp of fresh ginger, minced\r\n* 1/2tsp turmeric\r\n* 1/2tsp ground coriander\r\n* 1/2tsp **garam masala** \r\n* 1/2tsp mild chilli powder (add less if using standard chilli powder)\r\n* 400g (0.9Pounds) of chopped tomato sauce (one tin)\r\n* 2tsp sugar\r\n* 1/2tsp salt\r\n* 2,5tbsp yoghurt\r\n* fresh coriander to garnish\r\n\r\n### Ingredients for Crunchy Cauliflower:\r\n\r\n* medium-sized cauliflower (around 750g with leaves removed) cut into florets (cut biggest florets into half).\r\n* 1/2tsp salt\r\n* 1/2tsp paprika\r\n* 1/2tsp turmeric\r\n* 1/2tsp black pepper\r\n* 2 eggs\r\n* 100g (3.5oz) breadcrumbs\r\n* 0,5L (0.5quarts) vegetable oil for deep-frying (may need more if using deep-fryer) \r\n\r\n### Instructions for the Tikka Sauce:\r\n\r\n**1.** In the small saucepan melt **1tbsp of butter** and add **1 diced shallot**, sweat on medium heat for around **5 minutes**.\r\n\r\n**2.** Next, add **2 minced garlic cloves**, **1tsp of minced ginger** and cook for **1 more minute**.\r\n\r\n**3.** Add all spices, **1/2tsp turmeric**, **1/2tsp ground coriander**, **1/2tsp garam masala**, **1/2tsp mild chilli powder** and cook for another **minute**.\r\n\r\n**4.** Add **400g of chopped tomatoes**, **3tsp of sugar**, **1/2tsp of salt** and bring to simmer. \r\n\r\n**5.** Blend with a **hand blender** until smooth then finish by mixing in **2,5tbsp of yoghurt**.\r\n\r\n**6.** Taste and adjust, there should be balanced between sweetness and sourness.\r\n\r\n# Instructions for the Cauliflower Bites:\r\n\r\n**1.** Place **cauliflower florets** in the bowl and season with **1/2tsp of salt**, **1/2tsp paprika**, **1/2tsp turmeric**, **1/2tsp black pepper**. Mix until coated.\r\n\r\n**2.** In a small bowl whisk **2 eggs**. Dip each floret in the egg, then in **breadcrumbs** and place it on the plate ready for deep-frying.\r\n\r\n**3.** To deep-fry heat **0,5L of vegetable oil** in a small saucepan or deep-fryer to the temperature of **170C (340F)**. Fry a few florets at a time for around **2-3 minutes** or until golden brown. Once ready transfer onto a tray with a kitchen towel to remove excess fat, serve with sauce once all the florets are fried. Enjoy!\r\n\r\nBlog post:https://www.insightflavour.com/post/crunchy-cauliflower-bites-tikka-masala-sauce', 'strawberry-mascarpone-tart-with-port-glaze-352272.jpg', 3090),
(16, 'STRAWBERRY CAKE (recipe in comments)', '2021-02-20 00:00:00', 'food-posts-16', 'Fistul-a', 'Fistul-a@gmail.com', '*Link to the video-tutorial and full recipe with all details is provided at the end of the comment.*\r\n\r\n&amp;#x200B;\r\n\r\nThe strawberry cake requires 4 main preparations:\r\n\r\n* two layers of Savoyard biscuit\r\n* a dose of syrup for soaking the layers of Savoyard\r\n* Mousseline cream with vanilla\r\n* Chantilly cream for decoration\r\n\r\nIn addition, you will need about 500g of fresh strawberries of excellent quality, possibly large sized.\r\n\r\n**Ingredients for the Savoyard biscuit**\r\n\r\n* Flour (possibly weak W170): 150 g\r\n* Egg whites: 180 g\r\n* Egg yolks: 120 g\r\n* Caster sugar: 150 g\r\n* Icing sugar: 40 g\r\n\r\n**Ingredients for the Syrup**\r\n\r\n* Sugar: 70 g\r\n* Water: 12 cl\r\n* Kirsch: 2 cl\r\n\r\n**Ingredients for the Mousseline cream with vanilla**\r\n\r\n* Milk: 600 g\r\n* Vanilla bean: 1\r\n* Egg yolks: 120 g\r\n* Caster sugar: 180 g\r\n* Cornstarch: 60 g\r\n* Butter (at 18° C): 300 g\r\n\r\n**Ingredients for Chantilly Cream**\r\n\r\n* Heavy cream: 200 g\r\n* Icing sugar: 25 g\r\n* Preparation\r\n\r\nPreheat the oven to 180 °C and prepare the Savoyard biscuit. Whip the egg whites until stiff. When the egg whites are well whipped, gradually add the granulated sugar until the mixture is very firm. At this point gently add the egg yolks and whip again for 5 seconds. Sift the flour and add it by hand to the mixture (with a spatula), trying to mix the ingredients as best as you can.\r\n\r\nWhile the two layers of biscuit are cooling down, prepare the Mousseline cream and the syrup. For the syrup, mix the ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil, stirring periodically. Cook for 3 minutes, continuing to stir. For the Mousseline cream, divide both the butter and the sugar into two equal doses. Extract the seeds from the vanilla pod and heat the milk by inserting one of the two parts of sugar together with the seeds and the vanilla bean. You have to bring it to a boil and let it simmer for 5 minutes, so as to infuse the taste of vanilla into the milk. Meanwhile, in a bowl, whisk the egg yolks with the starch and the remaining sugar. After a while, to facilitate whisking, add a little hot milk. Remove the vanilla pod from the boiling milk and add the egg mixture, stirring vigorously with the wooden spoon. Cook over very low heat until the cream has thickened well, in any case for at least 2 minutes. Turn off the heat and add one of the doses of butter, continuing to stir until it has completely dissolved. At this point, the cream must be allowed to cool until it reaches room temperature. When the cream is cooled, put it in the mixer and start whipping it at high speed. Cut the remaining amount of butter into small squares and gradually add it to the cream, continuing to whip. When the mixture is completely homogeneous and uniform, the mousseline cream is ready.\r\n\r\nWash the strawberries and cut them in half vertically, trying to make pieces all the same height. Before you start cutting them, select the most beautiful strawberry, which you will leave aside so that you can use it for the final decoration. Take the ring and use it to cut two perfect circles of Savoyard.\r\n\r\nStart assembling the cake by inserting the acetate strip into the ring and inserting the various layers one after the other. Start with a layer of biscuit, which you will wet with a generous dose of syrup. Then, with the help of the sac-a-poche, make a first fairly thin layer of mousseline cream. Make a ledge of strawberries along the edge of the ring, placing the cut part of each strawberry in direct contact with the acetate. Cut the leftover strawberries into big pieces and fill the centre. Still using the pastry bag, fill each empty space with the Mousseline, starting from the edges of the cake, and make a final layer of cream over the strawberries. Place the second Savoyard biscuit on the cream, and wet this too with the syrup. Put the cake to cool in the refrigerator for at least 15 minutes and in the meantime prepare the Chantilly cream.\r\n\r\nWhip the cream in the mixer starting with a medium speed and gradually increasing until you reach the maximum speed. When the cream begins to grow in volume, gradually add the sugar. Continue whipping until smooth and satiny.\r\n\r\nTake the cake from the refrigerator, remove both the acetate and the ring. With the help of the spatulas make an even layer of cream on top of the cake.\r\n\r\n&amp;#x200B;\r\n\r\nVideo-Tutorial and full recipe:\r\n\r\n[https://guerinoscakes.wordpress.com/2021/02/19/strawberry-cake/](https://guerinoscakes.wordpress.com/2021/02/19/strawberry-cake/)', 'lemon-mint-braised-artichokes-352323.jpg', 4438),
(17, 'Potato and Leek Soup', '2021-02-19 00:00:00', 'food-posts-17', 'pangibear', 'pangibear@gmail.com', '**Potato and Leek Soup**\r\n\r\nFor full recipe, substitutions, variations, tips, &amp; tricks, visit: [https://maplewoodroad.com/food/potato-and-leek-soup/](https://maplewoodroad.com/food/potato-and-leek-soup/)\r\n\r\n### INGREDIENTS \r\n\r\n* 4 Tbsp butter\r\n* 4 leeks, trimmed and chopped to 1/8\"\r\n* 2 cloves garlic, thinly sliced\r\n* 1/2 tsp kosher salt\r\n* 1/2 tsp freshly cracked black pepper\r\n* 2-1/2 c chicken stock\r\n* 2-1/2 c water\r\n* 2 bay leaves\r\n* 1 Tbsp chopped flat-leaf Italian parsley (plus more for garnish)\r\n* 1 tsp fresh thyme leaves\r\n* 1 lb Yukon potatoes, thinly sliced\r\n* 1/4 c heavy cream\r\n* Salt and pepper to taste\r\n\r\n### INSTRUCTIONS \r\n\r\n* In a large pan, heat 4 Tbsp butter until it bubbles. \r\n* Then add the chopped leeks. Season with 1/2 tsp kosher salt and 1/2 tsp pepper. Stir occasionally for about 10 minutes until the leeks get really soft and the edges begin to brown. \r\n* Add garlic and stir for another couple of minutes. Taste before the next step. \r\n* Add 5 c liquid (I use 50% chicken stock and 50% water) and the herbs. Taste and see if you like the balance so far. Some stocks are saltier than others. \r\n* Crank up the heat to bring it to a quick boil, then reduce the heat and simmer for 5 minutes.\r\n* Add 1 lb of thinly sliced Yukon gold potatoes and let it simmer with the lid on for about 40 minutes. Stir occasionally.\r\n* The soup is done when the potatoes are very tender and starting to fall apart. We might still have to add some more salt and pepper. Potatoes soak up some salt. Taste again. Season with salt until you achieve the desired yumminess. If you like, add a pinch of cayenne pepper, which really makes it pop. \r\n* Serve in a bowl, add a splash of heavy cream (if desired), and top with some fresh flat-leaf Italian parsley.\r\n* If you prefer a creamy consistency, use an immersion blender and blend everything together before serving.', 'thyme-honey-glazed-ham-352289.jpg', 1851),
(18, 'Creamy Tadka Dal... the trick is in making a deep toasted Tadka as your topping.', '2021-02-19 00:00:00', 'food-posts-18', 'FineDiningJourno', 'FineDiningJourno@gmail.com', '[Step-by-Step Pics with Video](https://www.finedininglovers.com/recipes/ultimate-tadka-dal-recipe-step-step)\r\n\r\n**INGREDIENTS:**\r\n\r\n**Lentils**\r\n\r\n1 cup (240g), split moong yellow\r\n\r\n**Spring Water**\r\n\r\n4 cups (880ml)\r\n\r\n**Salt**\r\n\r\n1 1D2 tsp plus a pinch\r\n\r\n**Turmeric**\r\n\r\n1D4 tsp\r\n\r\n**To make the tadka**\r\n\r\n**Ghee**\r\n\r\n2 tbsp (heaped)\r\n\r\n**Cumin Seeds**\r\n\r\n1 tsp\r\n\r\n**Ginger**\r\n\r\n1 tbsp, grated\r\n\r\n**Tomato Puree**\r\n\r\n1 tsp, double concentrate\r\n\r\n**Asafoetida**\r\n\r\n1D4 tsp (optional)\r\n\r\n**green chilli**\r\n\r\n1, slit in half\r\n\r\n**Red Chili Peppers**\r\n\r\n2-3, dried (optional)\r\n\r\n**Red Chili Powder**\r\n\r\n1D4 tsp\r\n\r\n**Garam Masala**\r\n\r\n1D4 tsp\r\n\r\n**Coriander**\r\n\r\nHandful fresh leaves, chopped\r\n\r\n**STEPS**\r\n\r\n**Step 1**\r\n\r\nWash lentils 3-4 times until the water runs clear.\r\n\r\n**Step 2**\r\n\r\nDrain well and transfer into a pressure cooker.  Add water along with salt and turmeric and then mix.\r\n\r\n**Step 3**\r\n\r\nCarefully secure the lid on the cooker and place on a high heat (if your pressure cooker has different valve settings, place on the highest one). \r\n\r\nWhen the pressure cooker first releases steam, reduce the temperature to medium and cook for 3 minutes. Then turn off the heat and remove from the hob.\r\n\r\n**Step 4**\r\n\r\nAllow the pressure cooker to rest for 2 minutes. Allow the steam to escape from your pressure cooker by either releasing the valve or, alternatively, place your cooker under a running cold tap until all of the steam has released.\r\n\r\nCarefully remove the lid and check the lentils. The lentils should be soft and tender. Transfer to a serving bowl.\r\n\r\n**Step 5**\r\n\r\nTo make the tadka, heat ghee in a small saucepan (you will need to work quickly and continuously mix everything while making the tadka). When the ghee is hot, add cumin seeds and ginger.\r\n\r\n**Step 6**\r\n\r\nAdd tomato puree, asafoetida, green chilli, dried red chillies &amp; chilli powder. Mix continuously and bring the pan back on the hob. When you see a paste has formed, turn off the heat and drizzle on half of the tadka on the cooked dal. Mix well.\r\n\r\n**Step 7**\r\n\r\nThen drizzle on the remaining tadka as a garnish (without mixing). Finish with garam masala and fresh coriander leaves.', 'tandoori-chicken-238388.jpg', 2089),
(19, 'VIRAL TIK TOK PASTA ! ( Baked feta, tomato pasta ) quite simple and healthy', '2021-02-19 00:00:00', 'food-posts-19', 'manga_sole', 'manga_sole@gmail.com', 'INGREDIENTS\r\n\r\nFusilli \r\n\r\n1 ½ cups Cherry tomatoes \r\n\r\n400g feta cheese\r\n\r\nSalt and pepper \r\n\r\nDried Oregano \r\n\r\nDried basil\r\n\r\n2 cloves garlic \r\n\r\nSTEPS [here](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=h1lPvkUaxPE) \r\n\r\nEverybody welcome back to another video today we\'re going to do feta tomato pasta \r\n\r\n1. let\'s start off by washing cherry tomatoes \r\n2. after washing we could transfer them to oven safe dish and make a hole in the middle of tomatoes\r\n3. add your feta cheese inside \r\n4. Drizzle olive oil \r\n5. then add 2 pinches of salt and black pepper \r\n6. add dried basil and dried oregano and a few shakes of chili flakes\r\n7. some more olive oil cause why not \r\n8. Chop 2 cloves of garlic and add on top then it\'s ready for the oven. \r\n9. Baked at 425 degrees for 35 minutes \r\n10. after 35 minutes your tomatoes should be nice and chard \r\n11. smash everything together and give them a good mix \r\n12. Add pasta of choice \r\n13. and toss them around one more time just like it did with the sauce \r\n14. there you have it you got yourself a creamy tomato pasta for dinner', 'chocolate-fondue-with-candied-orange-peel-raspberries-and-almond-macaroons-237187.jpg', 1033),
(20, 'Taquera Salsa Stewed Beef with Cheesy Grits', '2021-02-19 00:00:00', 'food-posts-20', 'BushyEyes', 'BushyEyes@gmail.com', 'Recipe here originally: [Spicy Stewed Beef with Grits](https://www.triedandtruerecipe.com/2021/02/19/spicy-stewed-beef-with-grits/)\r\n\r\nThis was a really delicious, easy recipe. I might get hate for using salsa, but it\'s a really easy way to load your beef up with flavor with not too much effort. You can use any brand of taquera salsa (which is a taqueria style salsa...)\r\n\r\n**Ingredients:**\r\n\r\nStewed Beef\r\n\r\n* 2-3 pound chuck roast\r\n* 1 tablespoon avocado oil\r\n* 1 yellow onion, peeled and sliced into wedges\r\n* 1/2 cup beef stock\r\n* 28-ounce can whole peeled tomatoes\r\n* 10 ounce jar salsa taquera\r\n* Crushed red pepper to taste\r\n* 1 teaspoon brown sugar, more if you like a sweeter heat\r\n* Salt and pepper to taste\r\n\r\nCheesy Grits:\r\n\r\n* 2 cups water\r\n* 1 cup corn grits\r\n* 1 cup whole milk\r\n* 3 tablespoons butter\r\n* 1/2 cup sharp cheddar\r\n* 1 teaspoon paprika\r\n* Salt and pepper to taste\r\n\r\nFor Serving:\r\n\r\n* Minced scallions\r\n* Jalapenos en escabeche (aka pickled jalapenos)\r\n\r\n**Method:**\r\n\r\n1. Cook the chuck: Preheat oven to 350ºF. Pat the chuck dry and season all over with salt and pepper. Cut the steak into thirds.\r\n2. Heat the avocado oil in a wide pot over medium-high heat. Once shimmering, add the chuck and cook the steak pieces for 4-5 minutes per side until browned all over.\r\n3. Add the onion the skillet around the steak and continue cooking until the onion softens and begins to turn light golden brown, an additional 5-6 minutes.\r\n4. Pour in the beef stock and bring to a boil. Add the whole peeled tomatoes, salsa taquera, crushed red pepper, salt, pepper, and brown sugar. Bring to a boil and then turn off the heat.\r\n5. Cover the beef and transfer to the oven for 3 hours.\r\n6. Remove the pot from the oven and taste. Turn the oven to 275ºF.\r\n7. Season again to taste with salt, pepper, crushed red pepper, and more sugar, if you like. Return to the oven, uncovered, for 1 hour until the beef is completely falling apart. Add more liquid, as necessary, if the beef liquid evaporates too quickly.\r\n8. Shred the beef and keep warm.\r\n9. Prepare the cheese grits: Bring 2 cups of water to a boil. Stir in the grits and salt and reduce heat. Stir in the milk. Simmer, stirring often, for 20 minutes until thickened and tender. Stir in the butter, cheddar cheese, paprika, salt, and pepper. Turn off the heat and allow the grits to rest for 5 minutes.\r\n10. To serve: Divide the cooked grits between plates and pile the beef on top. Garnish with pickled jalapeños and minced scallions. Enjoy!', 'udon-noodle-salad-352230.jpg', 2468);

